     <font class="TallRed">Ok, enough about you...let's talk about me.<a name="108676918173056428">&nbsp;</a></font>
		<div class="blackjustified" style="background-color:#eeeeee;padding:5px 5px 5px 5px;border-top:3px solid #cccccc;border-bottom:1px solid #333333;border-left:1px solid #cccccc;border-right:1px solid #cccccc;">
          First of all, for those who haven't asked me personally...what happened to E3R??<br /><br />Well, funny story actually, heh, umm...I was scammed. It was freshman year, I was poor as hell and this domain registrar sent me something in the mail that said it would renew e3-r.com for 20$ cheaper than my current host. I was so excited over it that I never thought it could have been fake. The bastards took my 15$ and my domain. I was pissed off but relieved at the same time. At that moment in E3R history we were recieving tons of hits, all the *good posters* weren't interested anymore because of the nonsense that was evolving. Part of the problem was that one member of the DevlogikSymbiot was missing- the government moderator. We'll keep his name out of things but now we have a better more prevalent member who will keep things in shape and do it well.<br /><br />All of the talent left and continued posting in other places, and they continue to do so. I tried to keep up with most of them but we all kinda scrambled for something else. I kept myself rather busy with school work when I had to think of a topic for my 15 page Research paper. I chose to reexamine my theory of the Electronic Third and suddenly something clicked. The result lies <a href="http://www.devlogik.com/www/E3R_2/texts/josephburdick_theE3Rtheory.php">here</a> (comments welcome). After getting A's in both classes I used E3R in this semester (this layout being one final project) I decided heh, since I'm here, why not just continue and open it back up again? So I did, and here we are.<br /><br />"FSEVN" is making people a little curious. It's just a name. If you want to know any deep meaning behind it, it's just the key on the keyboard that was used for HELP on most DOS-based machines back when the primary langauge was BASIC. HELP seems fitting but it would confuse readers if that was my display name. E3R_J is a name that has been buried along with all of the drama that existed. I'm a new person now and thus, I deserve a new name for a new beginning. <br /><br />My powers as Owner of E3R aren't as strong as most would think. If a rule is ever adopted, it goes through the DevlogikSymbiot first. The team is composed of four guys and one female and everything I control they control with me. Oh, and by the way, the "Couples Rule" was scrapped before E3R hit the dust almost 2 years ago.<br /><br />I'm a Junior now at Virginia Commonwealth University. My major has been changed from Business to Marketing and I am currently working at <a href="http://www.ncpc.org">NCPC</a>, a non-profit organization in DC that is responsible for things that virtually every American has heard about. There I am the assistant of the Director and I am also working with the Web-design team as a designer consultant/marketer. <br /><br />Because of my new major at school and its requirement for a mac computer, my family is going to help me with the purchase of a brand-new dual processor G5 w/ a 20" Apple display. Right after E3R went down I became obsessed with mac systems and soon after became a huge advocate for open-source operating systems such as Linux and GNU software. Since, I have migrated serveral people to use software that I use on my windows systems. They enjoy them a lot and are learning plenty about the joys of screwing MicroSoft. Anyway, I need to sleep so I can wake up in about 5 hours to pack and run some errands. I leave today @ 5pm to D.C. where I begin my professional career.<br /><br />Before I go, I would just like to thank everybody who has posted and will post--as well as all my readers--if it weren't for you people I don't know how I would be in the situation that I'm in. With the help of E3R, which isn't just a website, its the PEOPLE, I have accomplished many things. Without it, I probably wouldn't have recieved this scholarship. So to all: <strong>thank you</strong>.<br /><br />Good night/morning.<br />
